# Module 1: Introduction to AI for Software Development – Participant Guide

## 📝 Overview
This module introduces AI fundamentals for software engineers, covering model types, ethical practices, and when to leverage AI tools in development workflows.

## 🎯 Learning Objectives
- Identify different types of AI models (LLMs, vision, reasoning)
- Understand autocomplete vs chat vs agent mode
- Develop a tool-agnostic mindset

## 🚀 Activities
1. Token counting exercise using OpenAI docs
2. Compare O1 vs GPT-4x outputs on a sample coding task
3. Map your workflow to identify when to use powerful models

